long_desc.thetext:
Beta 1.3 ISO image for ppc64le retrieved at: http://ppc.koji.fedoraproject.org/compose/24/Fedora-24-20160509.0/compose/Server/ppc64le/iso/
Checksum verified OK.
Tested with a VM. The ISO does not boot, following messages are issued:
E3404: Not a bootable device! Trying to load: from: disk1 ... No DOS disk-label found.

at least for the Fedora-Server-netinst-ppc64le-24_Beta-1.3.iso these files are missing > /images/netboot/TRANS.TBL > /images/netboot/ppc64.img
and same for the full iso

i make a check of the grub modules in 1.3. It seems there'are a lot of changes in boot/grub/powerpc-ieee1275 i'm not sure if it could be a cause for this issue.
i will attach the diff beta 1.2 and 1.3 in next comment
rebuild the same grub2 version in f23 buildroot fixes this issue
grub2-2.02-0.33.fc24 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 24. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-c4d43baacc
i tested the grub2-2.02-0.33.fc24.dh.1 with dan's fix and confirmed the fix. no boot issue anymore after update and call grub2-install
